Warnkowo  () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Nowogard, within Goleniów County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Nowogard,  north-east of Goleniów, and  north-east of the regional capital Szczecin.
For the history of the region, see history of Pomerania.
